  "prompt": "Can I have a laptop bag apart from the 7kg bag (which is allowed for free) in the cabin space for jet airways?",
  "response": "Jet Airways, like most airlines, typically allows passengers to carry one piece of hand luggage (cabin bag) and one personal item (such as a laptop bag, handbag, or briefcase) into the cabin. The **cabin bag** is subject to the **7 kg weight limit**, while the **personal item** is usually smaller and lighter.\n\nHowever, **it\u2019s generally expected that the combined weight of both items does not exceed the airline's overall limit**, which in this case is 7 kg. If your laptop bag is small and lightweight, it\u2019s usually acceptable as long as it doesn\u2019t push the total weight over the limit.\n\n### Important Notes:\n1. **Check Jet Airways' Specific Policy**: Policies can vary based on the airline, route, and class of travel. Always refer to Jet Airways' official guidelines or contact their customer service for the most accurate and up-to-date information.\n2. **Size Restrictions**: Ensure both your cabin bag and laptop bag meet the airline's size requirements for cabin luggage.\n3. **Security Screening**: Be prepared to place your laptop bag in the security screening tray at the airport.\n\nIf you\u2019re unsure, consider packing your laptop in your main cabin bag to avoid potential issues at the gate. Safe travels! \u2708\ufe0f",
